Premier-designate Bulent Ecevit said he would persist in the difficult task of convincing a key party leader to join forces in a secular coalition.
Ecevit, a veteran leftist, already has the support of another center-right party led by Mesut Yilmaz, whose government collapsed last week under the weight of a mafia scandal.
After failing to bring together political rivals in a coalition, Premier-designate Ecevit announced that he was returning his mandate to the Turkish president.
Ecevit, a veteran leftist, was called on to form a cabinet over two weeks ago after Yilmaz ' coalition government collapsed in a no-confidence vote in Parliament.
